mg compared with placebo were 17,602 pounds and 24,464 pounds respectively. 
Sensitivity analyses showed that these results were robust to changes of 
relevant input data.
CONCLUSION: Solifenacin 5 and 10 mg are cost-effective treatments in patients 
with overactive bladder.

