This research was undertaken to explore gender, religiosity, perceived 
time-left-to-live and the interactions between these variables as predictors of 
fear of death in 144 Atlantic Canadian students using the Multidimensional Fear 
of Death Scale (MFODS). Predictions about cause, age, marital status, and place 
