The cost-effectiveness of using hepatitis A/B combined vaccine versus hepatitis 
B vaccine alone for high-risk heterosexuals.

Rein DB(1), Weinbaum CM.

Author information:
(1)RTI International, 2951 Flowers Road, Atlanta, GA 30341, USA. drein@rti.org

Previous studies estimated that vaccinating high-risk heterosexuals (HRH) with 
combination hepatitis A/B vaccine was a cost-effective alternative to 
vaccinating HRH against hepatitis B alone. Since then, the incidence of 
hepatitis A has declined dramatically in the United States. We re-estimate the 
cost-effectiveness of this policy accounting for modern declines in incidence. 
